I"è	<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/rtanglao/rt-kits-api3/actions/runs/3584193643/jobs/6030554003">A few days ago</a> my Github Action for rt-kits-api3 broke becuase the default operating system for <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ubuntu-latest</code> chagned to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">22.04.1</code> from <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">18.04</code></li>
  <li>The easy way to fix was to change <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ubuntu-latest</code> to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ubuntu-18.04</code> but that will break in April 2023.</li>
  <li>The proper way to fix it for now until the ruby <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ffi</code> gem is fixed to work with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libffi7</code> is to install <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libffi6</code> (alongside 7l; <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">libffi6</code> is not part of Ubuntu 22.04 and 20.04 by default) manually using the following yaml in the Github Actions file:
```yaml</li>
  <li>name: Install libffi6
    run: |-
      curl -LO http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/main/libf/libffi/libffi6_3.2.1-8_amd64.deb
      sudo dpkg -i libffi6_3.2.1-8_amd64.deb
```</li>
  <li>For full details, see<a href="https://github.com/rtanglao/rt-kits-api3/issues/2#top">fix libffi7 issue before March 2023 when ubuntu 18.04 is deprecated #2</a></li>
</ul>

